WEBVTT

00:00:00.500 --> 00:00:01.700
Hi, I'm Rich.

00:00:01.800 --> 00:00:04.200
Let's submit a table for the 2022 Table Contest.

00:00:04.600 --> 00:00:06.800
Let's assume you've created the table that you want to share.

00:00:07.100 --> 00:00:09.100
That's the Table Contest's main point.

00:00:09.300 --> 00:00:11.800
We need to fill out a few things to get your table submitted.

00:00:11.800 --> 00:00:12.600
So let's do that.

00:00:13.000 --> 00:00:13.700
Table title.

00:00:14.300 --> 00:00:14.900
Usernames.

00:00:14.900 --> 00:00:18.900
You have to have an RStudio username to even submit.

00:00:18.900 --> 00:00:19.799
Just enter it here.

00:00:20.299 --> 00:00:22.600
Remember to use the at sign just before your username.

00:00:23.000 --> 00:00:23.900
I put mine in.

00:00:24.500 --> 00:00:25.000
Great.

00:00:25.299 --> 00:00:25.799
Authors.

00:00:25.799 --> 00:00:27.400
Include all authors if you can right here.

00:00:27.400 --> 00:00:28.600
Just comma separate them.

00:00:28.900 --> 00:00:29.700
Social links.

00:00:29.900 --> 00:00:34.000
If you're on Twitter, anywhere else, social, put in your links

00:00:34.000 --> 00:00:34.299
right here.

00:00:34.299 --> 00:00:36.400
You can use markdown styling for these links.

00:00:36.900 --> 00:00:39.500
We'll give special recognition to folks who are newer to

00:00:39.500 --> 00:00:43.200
data science. People that are new, less than one year or more.

00:00:43.400 --> 00:00:44.400
I am definitely more than one year.

00:00:44.400 --> 00:00:45.200
So I chose that.

00:00:45.200 --> 00:00:47.799
But if you are new, choose less than one year.

00:00:48.799 --> 00:00:49.700
Submission type.

00:00:50.400 --> 00:00:51.099
There's four.

00:00:52.000 --> 00:00:53.000
There's a single table example.

00:00:53.000 --> 00:00:53.700
That's what I have right here.

00:00:53.700 --> 00:00:54.599
It's one table.

00:00:54.799 --> 00:00:56.900
I just want to show everything I can in this one table.

00:00:57.799 --> 00:00:59.200
If you have something that's really long, you have lots of

00:00:59.200 --> 00:01:00.599
text and you're teaching people.

00:01:01.000 --> 00:01:02.400
That is most definitely a tutorial.

00:01:02.799 --> 00:01:04.900
For other, if your submission doesn't fit into the single

00:01:04.900 --> 00:01:07.599
table example or tutorial category, select other.

00:01:08.099 --> 00:01:09.000
We're recognizing this here.

00:01:09.000 --> 00:01:13.400
If your table is built with R and or Python, so you may have

00:01:13.400 --> 00:01:16.000
a scenario where you're getting the data all sort of like

00:01:16.000 --> 00:01:16.900
through Python.

00:01:16.900 --> 00:01:19.599
You're making the table with R or maybe doing the reverse.

00:01:19.599 --> 00:01:20.000
Who knows?

00:01:20.000 --> 00:01:22.199
Maybe you're just doing it all in Python, whatever.

00:01:22.199 --> 00:01:24.300
Choose, put the checkboxes here.

00:01:24.400 --> 00:01:25.500
What languages you used.

00:01:25.900 --> 00:01:26.599
Libraries.

00:01:26.800 --> 00:01:27.500
Packages.

00:01:27.800 --> 00:01:29.099
You need to use them to make tables.

00:01:29.400 --> 00:01:32.099
For this table example, I just use GT, so I'll put it there.

00:01:32.699 --> 00:01:35.300
You may use a bunch of these packages.

00:01:35.300 --> 00:01:36.199
You may just use one.

00:01:36.199 --> 00:01:38.900
Choose the one that you used for your example.

00:01:39.699 --> 00:01:40.300
Category.

00:01:40.800 --> 00:01:41.900
So there's four of these.

00:01:42.199 --> 00:01:43.099
Static HTML.

00:01:43.900 --> 00:01:44.500
One table.

00:01:44.599 --> 00:01:45.599
It's HTML table.

00:01:46.300 --> 00:01:46.900
Interactive.

00:01:46.900 --> 00:01:50.300
So your HTML table has things that you can sort of click on.

00:01:50.300 --> 00:01:52.699
You can filter, do all sorts of like really fancy things,

00:01:52.699 --> 00:01:53.500
which are interactive.

00:01:54.000 --> 00:01:54.900
That's what that's for.

00:01:55.400 --> 00:01:56.099
Static print.

00:01:56.099 --> 00:01:59.400
That is more or less things like LaTeX, things which are,

00:01:59.400 --> 00:02:00.599
you know, like Word documents.

00:02:00.599 --> 00:02:03.300
You're just writing tables to like some pages.

00:02:03.900 --> 00:02:05.000
They're not HTML at all.

00:02:05.699 --> 00:02:06.599
Interactive Shiny.

00:02:06.599 --> 00:02:10.399
That is most definitely HTML and you're basically using Shiny

00:02:10.399 --> 00:02:12.699
in that case, a table inside Shiny.

00:02:13.699 --> 00:02:14.600
So that's the category.

00:02:16.000 --> 00:02:16.899
Short description.

00:02:17.199 --> 00:02:20.300
Here we have two fields for a short and long description.

00:02:20.800 --> 00:02:22.199
Short and full, we're calling them.

00:02:23.000 --> 00:02:25.399
Just choose something that's short for the short description.

00:02:25.399 --> 00:02:29.000
Obviously tweet length, give like a good roundup of what

00:02:29.000 --> 00:02:32.399
your table is trying to do, what you used, what inspired

00:02:32.399 --> 00:02:33.899
you, all sorts of things like that.

00:02:34.199 --> 00:02:35.000
Just keep it short.

00:02:35.199 --> 00:02:38.699
For full description, you can go wild and just like tell

00:02:38.699 --> 00:02:42.699
everything about, tell us everything that you considered,

00:02:42.699 --> 00:02:44.300
what technologies you used.

00:02:44.699 --> 00:02:46.899
Just fully flesh it out in full description.

00:02:47.199 --> 00:02:50.300
And again, you don't have to completely have everything

00:02:50.300 --> 00:02:52.399
perfect in this form.

00:02:53.000 --> 00:02:54.500
This can be edited afterwards.

00:02:54.600 --> 00:02:55.100
Industries.

00:02:55.100 --> 00:02:57.500
If this table pertains to some particular industry like

00:02:57.500 --> 00:03:01.300
life science, finance, public sector, what have you, just mention

00:03:01.300 --> 00:03:01.699
it here.

00:03:02.100 --> 00:03:04.899
You know, we want to know if, you know, if this table pertains

00:03:04.899 --> 00:03:05.899
to a field like that.

00:03:06.300 --> 00:03:07.199
We care about that sort of thing.

00:03:08.199 --> 00:03:08.899
Code apostrophe.

00:03:08.899 --> 00:03:13.100
A lot of times you'll have your table code in a GitHub repo.

00:03:13.800 --> 00:03:15.399
I linked to one repo here.

00:03:15.399 --> 00:03:18.000
It doesn't really exist, but it's a repo nonetheless that

00:03:18.000 --> 00:03:18.800
could exist.

00:03:18.899 --> 00:03:22.800
Make sure you put your table code in a repo and share the

00:03:22.800 --> 00:03:24.000
link right here in this field.

00:03:24.699 --> 00:03:27.300
For a link to the table, we prefer that you use Quartopub.

00:03:27.800 --> 00:03:29.000
I have it right here.

00:03:29.100 --> 00:03:31.000
This is my table entry in Quartopub.

00:03:31.300 --> 00:03:34.199
We can share right out of Quartopub by hitting this share

00:03:34.199 --> 00:03:36.100
button and then copy link.

00:03:36.699 --> 00:03:37.500
And that's what I did here.

00:03:37.500 --> 00:03:39.600
I just copied it straight into here.

00:03:40.000 --> 00:03:40.600
Like so.

00:03:40.899 --> 00:03:44.000
You may be, you know, creating a shiny table, sorry, a shiny

00:03:44.000 --> 00:03:45.399
app with a table inside of it.

00:03:45.399 --> 00:03:48.199
So you might be using shiny apps and we accept other forms

00:03:48.199 --> 00:03:50.500
too, but you know, try to use Quartopub if you can.

00:03:50.699 --> 00:03:51.899
RStudio Cloud Project.

00:03:52.800 --> 00:03:58.199
You may opt to use RStudio Cloud to host your table code in.

00:03:58.800 --> 00:04:01.100
It's a great option for, you know, when you want people to

00:04:01.100 --> 00:04:03.699
want to share the table and you want people to interactively

00:04:03.699 --> 00:04:06.000
get in there and, you know, play with your code.

00:04:06.399 --> 00:04:08.699
I actually already have a cloud project set up with this

00:04:08.699 --> 00:04:09.300
table in it.

00:04:09.500 --> 00:04:11.399
I can grab the link right here in the browser.

00:04:13.100 --> 00:04:14.399
And I can put it right here.

00:04:14.500 --> 00:04:17.000
So basically it's going to look like this, rstudio.cloud

00:04:17.000 --> 00:04:19.299
content and some number which is your project.

00:04:19.899 --> 00:04:20.600
And that is it.

00:04:21.799 --> 00:04:23.000
Then you just gotta hit the done button.

00:04:23.799 --> 00:04:28.299
And what it does is it takes you to something like this.

00:04:28.299 --> 00:04:31.700
It's like right before you actually create the topic itself.

00:04:32.000 --> 00:04:34.399
So basically all the stuff that was in the form populates

00:04:34.399 --> 00:04:35.100
inside here.

00:04:35.399 --> 00:04:35.799
It's great.

00:04:35.799 --> 00:04:37.899
You really don't want to touch it at all.

00:04:38.100 --> 00:04:39.299
You just want to create the topic.

00:04:39.299 --> 00:04:40.299
So let's hit this button.

00:04:42.000 --> 00:04:44.500
And soon you'll get your entry and this is actually live.

00:04:44.500 --> 00:04:48.100
This is actually a posted topic on RStudio community.

00:04:48.299 --> 00:04:50.700
Here where you can edit your submission.

00:04:51.399 --> 00:04:52.100
Just right here.

00:04:52.100 --> 00:04:54.200
And then yeah, you can go in here and go to the full

00:04:54.200 --> 00:04:56.899
description, you know, add things like images to your

00:04:56.899 --> 00:04:57.600
description.

00:04:57.600 --> 00:05:00.399
You can add, you know, change the text totally up to you.

00:05:00.399 --> 00:05:02.299
You can save the edit or you can cancel out of it.

00:05:03.000 --> 00:05:04.200
You know, the option is there.

00:05:04.200 --> 00:05:08.600
Once you have it in here, your submission is entered and

00:05:09.399 --> 00:05:10.399
yeah, I hope you win.

00:05:11.299 --> 00:05:12.000
And that's it.

00:05:12.299 --> 00:05:14.299
I hope to see you in this year's table contest.

00:05:14.500 --> 00:05:16.399
If you're looking for ideas, we encourage you to check out

00:05:16.500 --> 00:05:20.100
Tale Gallery and to participate in the weekly Tidy Tuesday

00:05:20.100 --> 00:05:20.700
on Twitter.

